## Inter-Section Scroll Hints

A `<div class="section-arrow">` sits **between every pair of adjacent sections**. It contains an anchor linking to the next section's ID with a `fas fa-chevron-down` icon.

```html
<div class="section-arrow">
    <a href="#problem" aria-label="Scroll to next section">
        <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
    </a>
</div>
```

The first arrow (hero → tech-bar) uses an additional modifier class:

```html
<div class="section-arrow section-arrow--hero">
    <a href="#tech-bar" aria-label="Scroll to next section">
        <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
    </a>
</div>
```

### CSS

All section arrows use the same pulsing-circle style as the hero scroll hint. The `.section-arrow--hero` adds extra vertical padding so it sits a little higher above the tech-bar.

```css
.section-arrow {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    padding: 1.5rem 0;
}

.section-arrow--hero {
    padding-top: 2.5rem;
    padding-bottom: 1.5rem;
}

.section-arrow a {
    /* same circle/pulse style as .scroll-hint */
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    width: 42px;
    height: 42px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    border: 2px solid rgba(0, 212, 255, 0.4);
    background: rgba(0, 212, 255, 0.08);
    color: var(--accent-primary);
    text-decoration: none;
    animation: scroll-bounce 2s ease-in-out infinite, scroll-pulse 2s ease-in-out infinite;
}
```

**Non-negotiable:** Every pair of adjacent landing page sections must have a `.section-arrow` between them — never skip a gap.

