## "See It In Action" — Tab/Scroll Discoverability Hint

Above the tab bar, two small pill badges remind visitors they can interact:

```html
<div class="ss-click-hint">
    <span><i class="fas fa-hand-pointer"></i> Click a tab to explore</span>
    <span><i class="fas fa-arrows-up-down"></i> Scroll to read</span>
</div>
```

CSS — these match the `.section-label` pill style:

```css
.ss-click-hint {
    display: flex;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    justify-content: center;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
}

.ss-click-hint span {
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    background: rgba(0,212,255,0.06);
    border: 1px solid rgba(0,212,255,0.2);
    border-radius: var(--radius-full);
    padding: 0.3rem 0.85rem;
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.4rem;
}
```

