## Screenshot Showcase — "See It In Action"

The `#example` section shows real screenshots of the live application in a tabbed, scrollable frame.

### File locations

```
ui/static/img/screenshots/
├── tab-job-details.png
├── tab-your-fit.png
├── tab-strategy.png
├── tab-company.png
├── tab-cover-letter.png
├── tab-resume.png
├── tab-optimize-cv.png      # Optimize CV tab (re-capture live when chrome changes)
├── tab-interview.png
├── tab-mock-session.png     # Mock Session tab
└── tab-outreach.png         # Hiring Outreach tab
```

Each file is a **single merged PNG** (not multiple images stacked) that shows the full scrollable content of that tab. When updating screenshots, always produce one tall merged file per tab rather than multiple separate images — this avoids all seam/gap alignment issues.

### HTML structure

```html
<div class="screenshot-showcase">
    <!-- Tab bar -->
    <div class="ss-tabs" role="tablist">
        <button class="ss-tab active" data-ss-tab="job-details" role="tab" aria-selected="true">
            <i class="fas fa-briefcase"></i>
            <span>Job Details</span>
        </button>
        <!-- … 6 more tabs … -->
    </div>

    <!-- Browser chrome frame -->
    <div class="ss-frame">
        <div class="ss-browser-chrome">
            <div class="ss-dots"><span></span><span></span><span></span></div>
            <div class="ss-url-bar">
                <i class="fas fa-lock"></i>
                <span>rolemule.app / dashboard / applications / …</span>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="ss-panels">
            <div class="ss-panel active" id="ss-panel-job-details">
                <img src="/static/img/screenshots/tab-job-details.png" alt="…" loading="lazy">
            </div>
            <!-- … 6 more panels … -->
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
```

### CSS classes

| Class | Purpose |
|-------|---------|
| `.screenshot-showcase` | Outer wrapper — `width: 100%` (matches container) |
| `.ss-tabs` | Flex tab bar, rounded top corners, `overflow-x: auto`, `scrollbar-width: none` |
| `.ss-tab` | `flex: 1` — all tabs share equal width; active state uses `box-shadow: inset 0 -2px 0 var(--accent-primary)` |
| `.ss-tab.active` | Cyan underline, accent color, semi-bold |
| `.ss-frame` | Border + rounded bottom corners + drop shadow |
| `.ss-browser-chrome` | Fake browser top bar with dots and URL |
| `.ss-dots span` | Traffic-light circles (red / yellow / green) |
| `.ss-url-bar` | Pill-shaped address bar with lock icon |
| `.ss-panels` | Scrollable area — `max-height: 580px; overflow-y: auto; scroll-behavior: smooth` |
| `.ss-panel` | Hidden by default (`display: none`) |
| `.ss-panel.active` | Visible with fade-in animation (`ss-fade-in`) |
| `.ss-panel img` | `width: 100%; height: auto; display: block` |

### TypeScript (`ui/src/pages/landing.ts`)

```javascript
// Activate a tab by ID and scroll the panel back to the top.
function ssActivateTab(tabId) {
    ssTabs.forEach(t => {
        const isActive = t.dataset['ssTab'] === tabId;
        t.classList.toggle('active', isActive);
        t.setAttribute('aria-selected', isActive ? 'true' : 'false');
    });
    ssPanels.forEach(p => {
        p.classList.toggle('active', p.id === `ss-panel-${tabId}`);
    });
    if (ssPanelsContainer) ssPanelsContainer.scrollTop = 0;
}
```

Tab buttons use `data-ss-tab="<id>"`. Panel IDs follow `ss-panel-<id>`. No auto-advance — switching is fully manual.

### Mobile behaviour

```css
@media (max-width: 768px) {
    .ss-tab span { display: none; }   /* icon-only tabs */
    .ss-panels { max-height: 340px; }
}
```

### Non-negotiables

1. **Never stack multiple `<img>` elements** inside one `.ss-panel` — always merge into one tall PNG first to avoid seam/gap issues between screenshots
2. **Always use a single `<img>` per panel** — no `.ss-continuation` wrappers or crop hacks
3. **Tab labels must use `<span>` tags** so they can be hidden on mobile without hiding the icon
4. **`flex: 1` on `.ss-tab`** — never `flex-shrink: 0`; all tabs must share equal width
5. **Images are served from `/static/img/screenshots/`** — never inline base64 or CDN URLs
6. **`loading="lazy"`** on all screenshot `<img>` elements — these are large below-fold images
7. **`alt` text must describe the tab content** — "Job Details — At a Glance grid…" not just "screenshot"

### Updating screenshots

When the app UI changes and screenshots need refreshing:

1. Run the app locally and navigate to the application detail page
2. For each tab, scroll through the entire tab content
3. Take a **full-page or scrolling screenshot** of the tab content (one tall merged image per tab)
4. Save as `tab-{name}.png` directly into `ui/static/img/screenshots/` — overwrite the old file
5. No build step needed — screenshots are served as raw static files, not processed by esbuild
6. Hard-refresh the browser to verify (`Cmd+Shift+R`)
